text.tspan: Average years of schooling vs. expected years of schooling, 2017
Average number of years the population older than 25 participated in formal education. Expected years of schooling
are the number of years a child of school entrance age can expect to receive if the current age-specific enrollment
rates persist throughout the child’s years of schooling.
Source: Lee-Lee (2016), Barro-Lee (2018) and UNDP, HDR (2018), UNDP, HDR (2018)
